{
  "texts": [
    "One potential measure involves setting a maximum limit on the number of tickets that can be owned by a single wallet, thereby significantly impeding the operations of automated bots within the digital ticketing sphere.",
    "Additionally, measures could be implemented to restrict ticket resale to a price that does not exceed the initial purchase price.",
    "Moreover, royalties can be seamlessly incorporated into the system, with automatic payments to the NFT creator [10].Under the background of issues observed in the ticketing system during the 2018 Asian games, the authors in [40] proposed the integration of blockchain and RFID in ing a sports ticketing system.",
    "In the new proposed system the blockchain is used to maintain tamperproof tickets and act as a transaction validator, subsequently, the spectators are provided with a unique RFID wristband containing their ticket number, which would trigger a smart contract once they pass by the RFID gate readers to check the validity of their ticket.",
    "This system would eliminate ticket counterfeiting as well as reduce physical contact due to the outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic.In the study by Regner et al. [28], the prevalent issues in sports ticketing systems, including ticket fraud and inadequate regulation of secondary markets, were tackled."
  ]
}